  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it just brings to mind the-- the-- the-- the difference of-- of this-- of the situation that-- that made our normal state of-- of affairs, which was nothing but at best adequate under situation of-- of-- of-- of house and-- and factory and everything woven together and so on, which was abnormal and so on.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it looked like a palace by comparison when I looked at-- at what this young man was putting up with.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that is one aspect of it, just to show the contrast.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The other-- the other thing was that as soon as I finished school-- and at school, I was enrolled.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was first-- in the first year I arrived at school in Europe, 8, they immediately elected me as chairman of the class committee.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And by the year 10, I was the chairman of the Self Help Committee of the school, which was the only activity the school had on their all-school basis.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they picked on me to be the chairman for whatever reasons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and I was there till the very-- the very end.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The-- but as soon as I left school, when I still was in Bialystok, I was immediately involved in community especially the Zionist movement-- not the youth movement but the adult movement.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So right into adult movement, enrolling myself in the politics of the-- in the-- in that [POLISH] of-- of Bialystok, so to speak, of the election campaigns for the-- for the [POLISH], which was a-- a-- a fight, a political fight against the [POLISH], against the religious, and against the-- and with all the youthful enthusiasm and-- and innocence that went with it, I used to involve myself with all of these sort of things.",
      "word_count": 75
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So those were the friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
